Map Data Model Objects in a Data Space

Create connections between data lake objects (DLOs) in a data space and data model objects (DMOs). You can use only mapped fields and objects with relationships for segmentation and activation.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To map data objects:	Data Cloud for Marketing Data Aware Specialist

Before you map a data object to a data space, review Data Mapping to understand the requirements and DMO relationships.

In Data Cloud, go to the Data Streams tab.
Open the data stream that you want to map. The Data Mapping section shows all the data spaces that a DLO is associated with.
Click Start.
Under Data Model entities, click Select Objects.
On the canvas, the source DLOs are on the left, and the target DMOs are on the right. All standard DMOs are available for mapping.
To select a custom data model, go to the Custom Data Model tab, and click New Custom Object.
Review the object label, object API name, and fields.
Click Save.
To establish a mapping, select the field in the DLO, and click the related field in the DMO. A confirmation appears with an arrow connecting the fields.
Click Save.
